<html>
  <head>
    <style>
      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: black;
        color: white;
        font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
      }

      /* MENU (exact index match) */
      .menu {
        position: fixed;
        top: 18px;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translateX(-50%);
        z-index: 20;

        display: flex;
        gap: 28px;

        font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,
                     "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
font-weight: 300;
        font-size: 28px;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;

        color: rgba(240,240,240,0.78);
        mix-blend-mode: difference;

        pointer-events: auto;
      }

      .menu a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: none;
        opacity: 0.85;
        transition: opacity 200ms ease, transform 200ms ease;
      }

      .menu a:hover {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(-1px);
      }

      .menu a.active {
        opacity: 1;
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-underline-offset: 4px;
      }

      /* TOP VIGNETTE (unchanged) */
      .menu-vignette {
        position: fixed;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 140px;
        z-index: 15;
        pointer-events: none;

        background: radial-gradient(
          ellipse at top center,
          rgba(0,0,0,0.70) 0%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0.45) 35%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0.18) 60%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0.00) 100%
        );

        -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(
          to bottom,
          rgba(0,0,0,1) 0%,
          rgba(0,0,0,1) 50%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0) 100%
        );

        mask-image: linear-gradient(
          to bottom,
          rgba(0,0,0,1) 0%,
          rgba(0,0,0,1) 50%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0) 100%
        );
      }

      /* =====================================================
         UPDATED: SOFTER + WIDER CONTENT VIGNETTE
         ===================================================== */
      .content-vignette {
        position: fixed;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;

        width: 88vw;   /* slightly wider = smoother transition into image */
        height: 100vh;

        z-index: 2;
        pointer-events: none;

        background: linear-gradient(
          to right,

          rgba(0,0,0,0.78) 0%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0.68) 35%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0.52) 55%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0.32) 72%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0.14) 88%,
          rgba(0,0,0,0.00) 100%
        );
      }

      /* LAYOUT */
      .layout {
        display: flex;
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      .content {
        width: 65vw;
        padding: 90px 60px 60px 60px;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 3;
      }

      .block {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin-bottom: 28px;
        opacity: 0.9;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }

      .block a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-underline-offset: 3px;
      }

      /* RIGHT IMAGE */
      .bg {
        position: fixed;
        top: 100px;
        right: 100px;

        width: 705px;
        height: 620px;

        background-image: url("/mess_detail.png");
        background-size: cover;
        background-position: center;

        opacity: 0.9;
        z-index: 1;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>

    <div class="menu-vignette"></div>

    <div class="menu">
      <a href="/about">About</a>
      <a class="active" href="/folded-map">Folded&nbsp;Map</a>
      <a href="/media">Media</a>
      <a href="/research">Research</a>
    </div>

    <div class="content-vignette"></div>

    <div class="layout">

      <div class="content">

      <div class="block">
          "The Folded Map" is my doctoral research project at the DocArtes programme at the Orpheus Instituut in Ghent, 
          and within the research cluster "Resounding Libraries" led by Dr. Bruno Forment. 
         It explores polyphonic music as a way of thinking about the world. 
         By tracing connections between musical notation, visual perspective, and early scientific models 
         of reality, it investigates how different systems of representation shape what can be known, 
         imagined, and shared. Working across historical repertoires and contemporary artistic practice, 
         the project treats notation not simply as a record of music but as an active site of interpretation, 
         negotiation, and invention. Through research, composition, and performance, it reopens 
         questions about authorship, agency, and the nature of musical works themselves.
        </div>

        <div class="block">
          A full version of the research proposal is available here:
          <a href="/Hallock_Andrew_Research_Description.pdf" target="_blank">Download PDF</a>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="bg"></div>

    </div>

  </body>
</html>